<plot>This short shows how the city of Reading, Pennsylvania, would implement civil defense procedures to help residents survive a nuclear attack. Through a network of volunteers, makeshift hospitals would be set up, auxiliary police officers would maintain order, and other elements of the civil defense program would be put in place.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?029221</url></doc>
